techmeme.title: Sonos is laying off about 200 employees, or 12% of its staff, as it reorganizes to make its product teams "flatter, smaller, and more focused" (Mark Gurman/Bloomberg)
Email: Google is eliminating its goal of hiring more employees from historically underrepresented groups and reviewing some DEI programs (Miles Kruppa/Wall Street Journal)
Arm reports Q3 revenue up 19% YoY to $983M, vs. $946.7M est., royalty revenue up 23% YoY to $580M, and licensing and other revenue up 14% YoY to $403M (Max A. Cherney/Reuters)
Qualcomm reports Q1 revenue up 17% YoY to $11.67B, vs. $10.93B est., handsets revenue up 13% to $7.57B, net income up 15% to $3.18B, issues a strong Q2 guidance (Kif Leswing/CNBC)
Sources: SoftBank is in advanced talks to acquire Ampere in a deal that could value the Oracle-backed chip designer at about $6.5B, including debt (Bloomberg)
